    "title": "Scope Creep Prevention and Extraction Discipline",
    "content": "Rule established: extraction changes deployment boundary only. Same language, database engine, data model, business logic, API contract. One thing changes: where code runs. Inventory team's DynamoDB request illustrates pattern that will repeat across all extractions. Counter-examples show dual-variable changes (extraction + storage migration) create uncontrollable debugging and timeline bloat. Enforcement via written rule, consistent citation in architecture reviews, and empowered decision maker who can say 'no bundling' and have it stick. Teams that finish fastest resist improvement bundling; teams that stall enable it.",
