  },
  {
    "title": "Decision-Making Speed as Migration Bottleneck",
    "content": "Actual critical path constraint is not engineering speed but architecture decision velocity. Every extraction surfaces questions: service ownership boundaries, data model questions, whether something is audit-scoped or not, whether a feature blocks extraction or extraction blocks feature. Teams finishing fast have empowered decision maker (not committee) who can answer in a day and move forward. Teams stalling have decision-by-committee turning questions into month-long discussions. Decision maker role: empower to make calls, explain reasoning, enforce no-revisits (new questions OK, revisiting old decisions is not), actively resist scope creep and audit surprises.",
